                <h2>Common Myths About Growing Hair Faster</h2>
                <p>There is a great deal of misinformation on the internet regarding hair growth. Let us address some of the most common myths:</p>

                <p><strong>Myth 1: "Cutting your hair frequently makes it grow faster."</strong> — This is incorrect. Trimming only removes split ends and has no effect on the hair follicle or growth rate.</p>

                <p><strong>Myth 2: "Hair can grow 1 inch in a week."</strong> — This is biologically impossible. The maximum growth rate is approximately 0.5 inches per month. For a more in-depth look at this topic, read our <a href="how-to-grow-hair-in-1-week-reality-check.php">reality check guide on growing hair in 1 week</a>.</p>

                <p><strong>Myth 3: "Applying oil alone can bring back lost hair."</strong> — While oils can improve scalp health, they cannot regenerate hair from dead follicles. Clinical treatment is required for that.</p>

                <p><strong>Myth 4: "Hair growth supplements work like magic."</strong> — Supplements are only effective when your body has an actual nutritional deficiency. Taking supplements blindly is not only ineffective but can potentially be harmful.</p>

